messages.message:
i saw this unexpected `Visibility must be either \"public\" or \"private\"` error in a Cypress CI run  (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/19536/overview/99938992-8b06-4869-90c9-c4bf5cbddf94/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1747780322376&att=1)on Paul's PR - the API call does provide a valid `visibility` arg though, and the BE takes care of lowercasing this (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/7b19e88/webserver/api-server/src/py/instabase/api_server/handler/api/v1/repo.py#L68) when checking the validity of the arg

i'm not able to reproduce when manually creating a workspace in crafting-cyp either - maybe this is a flaky error?

cc @Xindi Xu fyi

Ahh, my bad. I updated the backend to support both casing and updated the frontend to use uppercase only. I forgot to re-run the deployment :sweat:
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/70788
It should be resolved after the deployment starting in 30 mins

> i'm not able to reproduce when manually creating a workspace in crafting-cyp either - maybe this is a flaky error?
Yea, because crafting-cyp has both frontend and backend from the commit before the above PR; while Cypress CI has frontend code with the PR but backend code without the PR
ah i see, agreed that this should be resolved after the next deployment!
Sorry for the interruption! Really hoping that we can get to use ib-dev-backend template for Cypress CI
